The clouds that arrived yesterday and brought these showers today are all part of the remnants of Hurricane Kay. These brought locally heavy rainfall and gusty winds to SoCal this past weekend.

A few rain showers have developed this morning in the Sierra Nevada, and in the Sacramento Valley near the Sierra foothills. It's been a wet start to our Monday in Chico, and Oroville could see a shower this morning as well. https://t.co/WE20zkTxgJ

@Alan_Mas A Tropical Storm hit LA in 1939, and brought strong winds & heavy rain to the southland. That storm is the only tropical system to ever make landfall in California. In 1858, the San Diego Hurricane just missed making a landfall, but it did bring strong winds and heavy rain.

@Alan_Mas Remnants of tropical systems impact us almost every year, but seeing an intact Tropical Storm off of California is definitely rare. I remember strong Hurricane Linda in 1998 was forecast to make landfall in SoCal as a Tropical Storm, but it swerved out to sea instead.
Here's a close up look at the #mosquitofire (bottom right) burning west of Lake Tahoe. This is what's causing our skies to be hazy/smoky today. https://t.co/8zzTByggLe

Tropical Storm winds have arrived in SoCal as well. Downtown San Diego is only reporting 20-30 mph gusts at 1pm, but in the mountains east of San Diego, Otay Mountain (3283' elev.) has reported a gust up to 81 mph!
A few other mountain stations nearby are reporting similar gusts. https://t.co/PLtj6oGbqw

Rain from #TropicalStormKay has arrived in Southern California.
Through 1pm, just about 1/4" of rain has fallen in San Diego, but in the mountains of eastern San Diego County, 2" to 3" of rain has already fallen. https://t.co/3jm3479lEa
Finally, the smoke from near the California/Nevada/Oregon border is the #BarnesFire , which is burning north east of Alturas in Modoc County.

All of the smoke in central California is from the #MosquitoFire west of Lake Tahoe, which exploded in size yesterday. Some of that smoke could drift our way.
(3/4)

Winds will blow most of this to the east by tomorrow.
